# Python — apps/engine (`src/` layered layout)

```
apps/engine/src/
  api/  workers/  →  services/  →  repositories/  →  models/
                          ↑
                       config/
```

All application code under `src/` only. Tests in `apps/engine/tests/`.

- **Business logic only in `services/`.** `api/` (HTTP) and `workers/` (jobs) are thin — no algorithms.
- **DB access only in `repositories/`** using `models/` ORM types.
- **Prompts only in `services/llm` and `services/distill`.**
- **Single datastore = PostgreSQL**; no new data system without an ADR.
- **Ground + confidence** on derived artifacts; abstain rather than hallucinate.
- Type hints everywhere; Pydantic from `contracts/`; colocated `test_*.py`.
- **Docstrings + WHY comments:** every function/method/class (including nested closures)
  and non-obvious control flow — see `python-docstrings-engine.mdc`.
